      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "From a libertarian perspective, private platforms are essentially private property, meaning the government generally lacks the authority to dictate how owners manage their internal spaces without due process. If you treat internet moderation as a form of censorship, you are mistakenly applying public law to private contracts, effectively forcing private entities to violate their users' rights under threat of fines. This approach ignores the fundamental distinction that users have limited rights on private property just as they do in a physical mall or private club, making heavy-handed regulation a violation of both property and liberty.",
