    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. So basically, any attempt to force these platforms to follow certain moderation rules is just the state meddling in private business to control speech. Do you think there's any valid justification for these regulations, or is the whole concept of government-mandated internet moderation fundamentally incompatible with a free society?",
