      "content": "While proponents of regulation argue that platforms must balance free speech with safety to prevent harm, this justification often fails because it ignores the existence of third-party moderation tools and the platform's inherent right to set community standards. Furthermore, the current regulatory approach is fundamentally incompatible with a free society because it conflates private property management with state censorship, thereby eroding the very liberties those laws claim to protect. Ultimately, true freedom on the internet requires preserving the distinction between public discourse and private property, allowing users to self-govern without state coercion.",
